caption: The place offers a vast variety of fresh food. I like dining here. Employees are always very nice, rates are fair and the spot is always well organised.

Good Cantonese style food

Good restaurant for traditional Cantonese dishes. Very tasty and fresh. Always packed during dinner hours. Limited seating. Newly expanded 2nd floor for additional seating. Staff always tries to be attentive even though they are usually overly busy. Love the salt and pepper squid and the ox tail stew. Famous for their eel rice casserole.

Home of its infamously lovely prized eel casserole, has kept my family coming back regularly for years! Service is good, too, which for Canto restaurants nearby is a stellar unique factor, but the food is what's so fresh, authentic, solid, and beloved.

EDIT: The store has reopened with a Grade Pending score.  This means they received either a B or C grade and will attempt to appeal their score.  Hopefully this means they are working to improve their food safety.  CLOSED by Dept of Health and Mental Hygiene.  According to the DOH this means there are uncorrected or too many health hazards.  I have attached the public results of their last inspection in 8/2017 as well as their 4/2018 inspection from when they closed.  Hopefully if they reopen, they will address these concerns.

I feel so disappointed today! The waitress services so terrible! We were there almost done never see anyone came change the dishes,and ice water is empty, didn't refill it! I saw the waitress playing the game during the working time! Food prices are expensive as portions serving so little as usual! When I got my bill Didn't show state sale tax amount on the check, I completely didn't like the service, but Still tipped $5 Cash As the check $59, almost 10% , the waitress still pushed me pay more $5, it is so ridiculous I didn't want pay more! So funny the female owner see the all , keep the mouth closed. I have to say that I will call the police, then just let us leave! Never come back! Don't waste your money!
